social_posts.post_text: Great week at the @comedycellarusa in Las Vegas. Not a fan of the Las Vegas Strip so I try to get away everyday.  I dragged city boy @joshadammeyers and @trentoncomedy out into the desert to do some-off-roading, bouldering, hiking and to visit some hot springs. Still the most fun I have is hanging out with @mark_coco_cohen. Also got a chance to catch up with two amazing OG’s from the @crossfit world, @zach__af and @tommyhacksaw and worked out @thestripcrossfit.
Hey Southbay, Im at @roostertf this week. It’s one of my all-time favorite clubs and they just reopened after a massive renovation. Come hang out!

What a great Christmas gift. This is my favorite show of the year in my favorite place. Can’t wait to see you. Tickets at eddieifft.com. Two shows 4pm and 8pm

Throwback to my first appearance on the Joe Rogan  Experience. This was episode #77 of the @joerogan show. This was recorded in February of 2011. Even at that time it was one of the most successful podcasts on the internet. I felt like it was the 80’s and I was asked to sit on the couch with Johnny Carson. To this day, nothing has done more for my career. Joe has helped the careers of so many comedians like myself and I am eternally grateful. I just wish I took a picture of that kangaroo.

So many amazing comics on this show I couldn’t even fit myself on the poster. This is not one you will want to miss. February 17. If you haven’t been to the Bourbon Room yet, you’re missing out. It’s an amazing room to watch comedy and this lineup is sick dude. Totally sick bro. Zero Chinese weather balloon jokes I promise!!! Get your tickets now! It always sells out. Tickets at Bourbonroomcomedy.com

I never wanted to produce a show ever. Always thought it would be too much of a hassle. After the pandemic ended I was asked to do one at the @thecomedystore and just did it for shits and giggles. I forgot how fun it was to hang out with really really funny people and see them at their best!  The idea was just to have a good time. I didn’t realize that it would become this popular. It blows my mind and I am super grateful. So glad that people are having such a great time. This one on the 20th is such a great line-up and I say it every time, but it’s true. Get your tickets, because this will sell-out!! https://www.showclix.com/event/eddie-ifft-february20th

Joe Rogan is right. I need new friends!

My Eddie Ifft and Friends show is going so well that we are franchising. I mean doing it in other locations March 10 we will be doing it at the Ice House in Pasadena. The Ice House has just re-opened after remodeling. It was already one of the best comedy clubs in the world, and now I hear it’s even better. I have an incredible lineup.
Darrell Hammond 
Momo Rodriguez 
Jiaoying Summers
Mark Serritella 
Get your tickets now at https://embed.showclix.com/event/ice-house-eddie-ifft

I’d like to thank all these people ahead of time for opening for me and hope that they all know that I have a no eye contact or handshaking policy backstage. This will be sold-out in the next 5 minutes, so get your tickets now!!! Bourbonroomcomedy.com. Also please refrain from bringing “I ❤️ You Eddie” posters. I also have a no standing ovation policy after my sets to respect the other comedians. Tailgating will be confined to the parking lot across the street on Vine.

Last day to get your pre-sale tickets for my homecoming show. I lived almost half my life in Pittsburgh and even went to college there. I started my comedy career there and it’s always the best to go home and see all my friends and family and perform for them. This show is like no other with all the inside jokes and it’s a big venue. Please send this out to all the Yinzers you know. I want this to be a crazy one. Tickets are available at eddieifft.com. Presale discount code ends today. Code is VIP

Tickets are available at eddieifft.com

Vail Colorado. This was one of my favorite shows of the year last year and we are doing it again!!! Most comedians have dreams of playing Madison Square Garden or Carnegie Hall. Just give me ski resorts and beach towns and I’m in heaven! Disney world calls itself the happiest place on earth. I think Vail next Thursday night April 6 at the Shakedown Bar should get that distinction. It sold-out last year. Let’s do it again next Thursday.
Steamboat Springs Colorado. Apres ski with apres me. I’ll be back in Steamboat on April 7&8. Tickets were selling so fast we added a second show. Get your tickets at Steamboatcomedy.com
Not Hawaii. I’m home between Mexico and Colorado. See ya in Vail tues-thurs and Steamboat Springs fri-sat!!! Tickets to all my shows are at eddieifft.com
Vail Colorado this Thursday night I’m bringing my stand-up comedy show to the Shakedown Bar. This show sold-out last year and hopefully will this year too!  Come have some laughs and drinks with me!
